Restrictions

This license does not include the right to replicate a similar or competing product/service, using the design assets provided by Notion Avatar Maker.

It is not allowed to re-package the existing set of avatar designs, or re-brand it under another product or service name.

When used in other products and services, Notion Avatar Maker should always be treated as an addition to your product, but not as the product on its own.

Example in a digital world: It is not allowed to create and sell an NFT collection of avatars generated with the Notion Avatar Maker library, since that would be considered a direct competitor to the official Notion Avatar Maker NFT collection.

Example in a physical world: It is not allowed to open an officially-looking Notion Avatar Maker bar or a restaurant, or to sell official Notion Avatar Maker toys, etc. But if you are opening a bar under your own brand, you can use Notion Avatar Maker in all areas of your visual communication. Similarly, if you sell your own custom line of toys, avatars from Notion Avatar Maker can be parts of your toy world.


Attribution

You can use Notion Avatar Maker with or without the attribution.

A similar attribution is appreciated: Avatars by Notion Avatar Maker

On websites, insert the attribution on the page where the avatar is shown. This can be placed next to the image or on the footer of the website.

On physical items, add this attribution to the description of the final work or product so that the authorship of Notion Avatar Maker is known. For instance, add to the description on a web store's product page, or in the printed description of a physical item.

Place the attribution on the app's about or credits page and on the description page on the app store.

Insert the attribution line on the post or post comments on social networks.


